bib_record.title: Nuclear mass and charge distributions in the cold region of the spontaneous fission of Cf-252

free_txt: .The fragment masses and total kinetic energy were
determined by applying relevant gates in the data.
The contribution of each nuclear charge state to the
isobaric yield was obtained by convolution of the
experimental charge distributions.
.Corrections were applied for the energy loss of the
fragments in the Ni-foil, for the grid inefficiency,
and for the pulse-height defect.
The fission-fragment detection was done with a
frisch-gridded twin ionization chamber. The sample was
mounted in the cathode plane in the center of the
chamber. The distance between the cathode and the
grids was 46 mm and the distance between the grids and
the anodes was 12 mm. The effective diameter of the
grids was 15 cm and the outside diameter of all
electrodes was 18 cm. The chamber was operated with a
methane gas flow of 0.1 l/min, while the gas pressure
was kept at 64 kPa. A mass resolution of 0.4 u was
observed in the near cold-fission region.
Relative fission yield measurement
.The sample was a commercially available Cf-252 source,
vacuum evaporated on a 120 microgram/cm2 thick nickel
foil. The target spot was 8 mm in diameter and the
source strength was 150 fissions/sec.
